labels.label:
Connector - Excel file stored in AWS S3 to Snowflake

This connector extracts data from a specified Excel file stored in AWS S3 object and loads it into Snowflake.

Requirements:
- the connector uses an Access Key to authenticate with AWS user
- the connector performs a full offload: on each scheduled ingestion, data from the destination table is deleted and then re-ingested.

parameters.description: The database where data retrieved from Excel file will be persisted. It must already exist in Snowflake.

parameters.description: Snowflake role that is going to be used by the connector.
parameters.name: Snowflake Role

parameters.description: The prefix of the table in the destination schema where data retrieved from Excel file will be persisted. The table will be created automatically by the connector.
parameters.name: Destination Table Prefix

parameters.description: Protection type on the Excel file. Can be either "UNPROTECTED" if the file is unprotected, or "PASSWORD" if the file is protected with password.
parameters.name: Protection Type

parameters.description: The A1 notation of the comma-separated ranges to retrieve values from. For example: Sheet1!A1:B2,Sheet2!D4:E5,Sheet3. The first row in selected range must represent column names.
parameters.name: Ranges

parameters.description: The S3 bucket from which the Excel file should be fetched.
parameters.name: S3 Bucket

parameters.description: List of comma-separated object keys within the S3 bucket that contain Excel files to fetch, e.g. "file1.xlsx,file2.xlsx".
parameters.name: S3 Object Keys
